Spencer (nibalizer) Krum has been using Puppet since 2010. He works for HP doing OpenStack and Puppet things. Spencer coordinates the local DevOps user group in Portland and volunteers for an ops-training program at Portland State University called the Braindump. Spencer helps maintain numerous Puppet modules on the pdxcat and puppet-community github/forge namespaces. Spencer is Puppet certified and a co-author of Pro Puppet (2nd ed) from Apress. His new book, Beginning Puppet, with William (blkperl) Van Hevelingen and Daniele (Daenney) Sluijters, is due out next year.
